---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title="Architecture | Ionyx Framework">
	<section class="py-20 hero-gradient">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
				<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
					Architecture
				</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
					Deep dive into Ionyx's minimalist architecture and how it achieves high performance with low resource usage.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-20">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-16">

				<div class="glass-dark p-8 rounded-xl">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Overview</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Ionyx follows a minimalist architecture focused on performance, security, and developer experience.
						The framework consists of four main components working together seamlessly.
					</p>
					<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
						<pre class="text-sm font-mono text-green-400"><code is:raw>Ionyx Architecture:
├── 🦀 Rust Backend (Core)
│   ├── WRY (WebView)
│   ├── TAO (Windowing)
│   └── IPC Bridge
├── ⚡ CLI Tool (Development)
│   ├── Process Orchestration
│   └── Environment Management
├── 🌐 Frontend (Any Framework)
│   ├── Vite (Development)
│   └── Web Technologies
└── 📦 Build System (Production)
    ├── Cargo (Rust)
    └── Static Assets</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-dark p-8 rounded-xl">
					<div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-6">
						<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
							<span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">🦀</span>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Rust Backend</h2>
							<p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
								The heart of Ionyx is written in Rust, providing memory safety, high performance, and native system access.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">WRY WebView</h3>
							<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
								<li>• Cross-platform WebView (WebKit/Gecko)</li>
								<li>• Chromium on Windows/Linux</li>
								<li>• WebKit on macOS</li>
								<li>• Native JavaScript execution</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">TAO Windowing</h3>
							<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
								<li>• Cross-platform window management</li>
								<li>• Native OS integrations</li>
								<li>• Event handling</li>
								<li>• GPU acceleration</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">IPC Bridge</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
							Bidirectional communication between Rust backend and frontend JavaScript.
						</p>
						<pre class="text-sm font-mono text-purple-400 bg-slate-900 bg-opacity-50 p-4 rounded"><code is:raw>// Frontend side
const response = await window.ionyx.invoke({
  command: 'bridge.getApps',
  payload: {}
});

// Rust side
pub async fn handle_request_with_response(&self, request: String) -> Result<()> {
    let ipc_request: IpcRequest = serde_json::from_str(&request)?;
    match ipc_request.command.as_str() {
        "bridge.getApps" => {
            // Handle getApps command
        }
        _ => {}
    }
}</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-dark p-8 rounded-xl">
					<div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-6">
						<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-blue-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
							<span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">⚡</span>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">CLI Development Tool</h2>
							<p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
								Automated development workflow with process orchestration and environment management.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Process Orchestration</h3>
							<pre class="text-sm font-mono text-green-400"><code is:raw>$ ionyx dev
├── Start Vite dev server
├── Wait for port 5173
├── Set IONYX_URL=127.0.0.1:5173
├── Launch Rust app
└── Monitor processes</code></pre>
						</div>

						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Environment Management</h3>
							<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
								<li>• Automatic dependency installation</li>
								<li>• Port conflict resolution</li>
								<li>• Single instance locking</li>
								<li>• Cross-platform compatibility</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-dark p-8 rounded-xl">
					<div class="flex items-start space-x-4 mb-6">
						<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-green-500 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
							<span class="text-white font-bold text-lg">🌐</span>
						</div>
						<div>
							<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Frontend Agnostic</h2>
							<p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
								Use any frontend framework or vanilla JavaScript. Ionyx adapts to your preferred stack.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
							<div class="text-2xl mb-2">⚛️</div>
							<div class="text-blue-400 font-semibold">React</div>
						</div>
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
							<div class="text-2xl mb-2">🟢</div>
							<div class="text-green-400 font-semibold">Vue</div>
						</div>
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
							<div class="text-2xl mb-2">🧡</div>
							<div class="text-orange-400 font-semibold">Svelte</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Development vs Production</h3>
						<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-purple-400 font-semibold mb-2">Development</h4>
								<ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1">
									<li>• Hot Module Replacement</li>
									<li>• Source maps</li>
									<li>• DevTools integration</li>
									<li>• Fast rebuilds</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div>
								<h4 class="text-green-400 font-semibold mb-2">Production</h4>
								<ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 space-y-1">
									<li>• Minified bundles</li>
									<li>• Tree shaking</li>
									<li>• Asset optimization</li>
									<li>• Single binary</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-dark p-8 rounded-xl">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Security & Performance</h2>

					<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-400 mb-4">🛡️ Security</h3>
							<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
								<li>• Memory safe Rust backend</li>
								<li>• Sandboxed WebView</li>
								<li>• Controlled IPC channels</li>
								<li>• No Node.js runtime</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div class="bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-4">⚡ Performance</h3>
							<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
								<li>• Sub-2MB binary size</li>
								<li>• <30ms startup time</li>
								<li>• Low memory footprint</li>
								<li>• Native performance</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="mt-6 bg-slate-800 bg-opacity-50 rounded-lg p-6">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Build Process</h3>
						<pre class="text-sm font-mono text-yellow-400"><code is:raw>Development Build:
├── Frontend: Vite HMR server
├── Backend: Cargo incremental build
└── Output: Hot-reloaded app

Production Build:
├── Frontend: Static asset generation
├── Backend: Cargo release build
├── Assets: Embedded in binary
└── Output: Single executable</code></pre>
					</div>
				</div>

			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>